-- England Beats Australia in Third Straight Ashes Cricket Series
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 2013-08-12T18:51:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-12/england-beats-australia-in-third-straight-ashes-cricket-series.html
England defeated  Australia  by 74
runs in the fourth cricket Test to clinch the Ashes series as
 Stuart Broad  took 11 wickets.  Broad took 6-50, after taking 5 in the first innings at
Chester-le-Street as the hosts won their third straight Ashes
series. England took a 3-0 lead in the five-match series after
Australia was all out for 224 today.  England scored 238 in its first innings, and the visitors
took a 32-run lead in response. Australiaâ€™s  Ryan Harris  took
seven wickets to limit the hosts to 330 all out in their second
innings, setting a victory target of 299 runs.  The hosts had already retained the Ashes by winning the
first two Tests, with the third one ending in a draw. The final
match in the series starts Aug. 21 at the Oval in London.  To contact the reporter on this story:
